name: Walla Walla County HD- COVID Provider
vaccines: Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine, Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
**THIS CLINIC IS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY FOR 1st DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS for all qualifying individuals aged 12 years & over. Parental/Guardian consent is required for 12 – 17 year olds, parent/guardian consent and signature can be completed on-site or in the final screen of the online registration process. This clinic is at the Providence Southgate Medical Park main building (the former Walla Walla General Hospital) 1025 South 2nd Ave. Participants are advised to stay to their right as they enter the campus and proceed to the main entrance, instead of going to Urgent Care. COVID vaccine is not available in Urgent Care.
Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.

** ESTA CLÍNICA ES CON CITA SOLAMENTE PARA LAS VACUNAS DE LA PRIMERA DOSIS DE PFIZER para personas calificadas de 12 años en Adelante.  Se requiere el consentimiento de los padres / tutores para los jóvenes de 12 - 17 años, las firmas y el consentimiento en la pantalla de registro final.** Esto será en el edificio principal de Providence Southgate Medical Park, (antes conocido como el Hospital General de Walla Walla)1025 Sur 2nd ave.  Se recomienda a los participantes que se mantengan a su derecha al ingresar y que se dirijan a la entrada principal, en lugar de ir a Atención de Urgencia.  La Vacuna COVID no está disponible en Atención de Urgencias. **
El cubre bocas es requerido. Si no tiene un cubre bocas, se le proporcionará una.  
Esperamos verlo. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.

name: Lincoln Creek Lumber Clinic
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info: ****This is a JOHNSON & JOHNSON single dose, Pfizer 1st/2nd dose and Moderna 2nd dose vaccine clinic. **** and is by appointment or walk in.  Please note: Johnson & Johnson and Moderna vaccine can only be administered to individuals 18 years of age or older according CDC requirements. Pfizer has been authorized for ages 12 – 17 with parental authorization. This clinic is located at and hosted by the Lincoln Creek Lumber office in Chehalis in partnership with Lewis County Department of Health and Social Services, WA Department of Health and WA National Guard. This is a walk-in location. Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind. **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation. Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided. Please do not come if you are feeling ill.  It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. **Masks are still required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Arlington Airport Covid-19 Vaccine Site
info:
*************THIS IS A PFIZER CLINIC********** 

Everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination. 

Please also note that, even if you are otherwise eligible, you must be 18 or older for the Moderna or Johnson & Johnson vaccine, and 12 or older for the Pfizer vaccine (parent/guardian must be present to sign the consent form). 

Appointments are highly recommended but not required. Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves. 

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
